full_text: Succeed Insurance employees occasionally need to search for activities of a particular type, such as litigation or approval activities. This capability is not present on the activity search screen in the base configuration, so I will add it. I'll log out of ClaimCenter and navigate to Guidewire Studio. If I look at the activity entity, I see that type is a type key, referring to the activity type type list. Now I'll add that type list to the activity search criteria entity. Activity search criteria is a read-only, or final, file. I will have to extend the file to add the new search criterion. I need to add a new type key element. Its name is activity type, with the SI suffix for succeed insurance. It refers to the activity type type list. And it is not a required value, so I will set NULL OK to true. Finally I'll give it a quick description. Finally I'll give it a quick description. Now I'll navigate to search config.xml. Under the existing activity search criteria, I add a new criterion element. The property is the type code I added, activity type underscore SI. Next, I'll add a target property. This is the property whose value must be matched in the type list, which is type. The match type is EQ, signifying that it must be an exact match to the type list. Before I add the new search criterion to the user interface, which is the subject of the next demo, I will regenerate the SOAP files. So I stop the server. In a command prompt window, I navigate to the Claim Center home directory. Here I type the GWB command that starts the SOAP generation. This concludes the configuring search criteria demonstration.
